        <p begin="00:10:16.120" end="00:10:18.080" tts:direction="ltr">cream, Aggie strawberry ice</p>
        <p begin="00:10:18.080" end="00:10:21.635" tts:direction="ltr">cream over the comparable product of their
<br />competitor.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:21.635" end="00:10:24.650" tts:direction="ltr">Creamery, and then in blind taste test.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:24.650" end="00:10:29.130" tts:direction="ltr">Here's that. Every aspect of flavor and on
<br />overall impression.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:29.130" end="00:10:31.210" tts:direction="ltr">Even when the ratings were close,</p>
        <p begin="00:10:31.210" end="00:10:34.450" tts:direction="ltr">enough not to be statistically significant
<br />ages cream was</p>
        <p begin="00:10:34.450" end="00:10:38.790" tts:direction="ltr">still never rated higher in any category.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:39.070" end="00:10:42.810" tts:direction="ltr">This provides a little more context.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:42.810" end="00:10:44.870" tts:direction="ltr">It gives you a different chart type.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:44.870" end="00:10:48.570" tts:direction="ltr">It celebrates those wins and</p>
        <p begin="00:10:48.570" end="00:10:54.205" tts:direction="ltr">provides maybe your manager with something
<br />else besides just a table.</p>
        <p begin="00:10:54.205" end="00:10:59.060" tts:direction="ltr">So that is the scenario scenario A and B,</p>
        <p begin="00:10:59.060" end="00:11:04.860" tts:direction="ltr">and hopefully this just cements the
<br />ability that you now have to tell</p>
        <p begin="00:11:04.860" end="00:11:11.620" tts:direction="ltr">a story with data no matter where or what
<br />circumstances you find yourself in.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
